Privacy Policy
Effective Date: [01-01-2025]

Welcome to Cook Z! Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our app to save and browse food recipes.

1. Information We Collect
Personal Information: To access the content in Cook Z, you are required to log in using your email address.
Usage Data: We may collect non-identifiable information about how you use the app, such as session duration and interactions, to improve our services.
2. How We Use Your Information
Your information is used solely for the purpose of providing and improving Cook Z services, including:

Granting access to in-app recipes and personalized features.
Allowing you to save, organize, and retrieve your recipes.
We do not sell, share, or disclose your personal information to third parties.

3. Data Storage and Security
All your personal data and saved recipes are securely stored in Firebase, a trusted and reliable cloud platform. Firebase provides encryption and security measures to ensure the safety of your data.

Your data is only accessible to you through your login credentials.
Cook Z does not access or share your stored data without your consent.
4. Third-Party Services
Cook Z uses Firebase for authentication and data storage. Firebase operates in compliance with industry-standard security and privacy practices. You can learn more about Firebase's privacy policy here.

5. User Control and Data Retention
